  "prompt": "How do I get placed in NYK shipping after completing my GME?",
  "response": "To get placed in NYK (Nippon Yusen Kaisha) shipping after completing your GME (Graduate Marine Engineering), follow these steps:\n\n1. Ensure strong academic performance during your GME\n\n2. Build a professional maritime resume highlighting:\n- Academic achievements\n- Internship experiences\n- Technical skills\n- Maritime certifications\n\n3. Network strategies:\n- Attend maritime job fairs\n- Connect with NYK representatives\n- Join maritime professional groups\n- Use LinkedIn networking\n\n4. Apply through official channels:\n- NYK's official website\n- Maritime recruitment portals\n- Campus placement programs\n- Direct email applications\n\n5. Prepare for recruitment process:\n- Technical interviews\n- Marine engineering knowledge test\n- Personal interview\n- Medical fitness assessment\n\n6. Required certifications:\n- Completed GME\n- Merchant Navy Certificate of Competency\n- Valid passport\n- Necessary medical certificates\n\n7. Consider additional qualifications:\n- Foreign language skills\n- Advanced technical certifications\n- Extra maritime courses\n\n8. Stay updated about NYK recruitment:\n- Follow their official website\n- Subscribe to maritime job platforms\n- Maintain professional contacts\n\nPersistence and preparation are key to securing a placement with NYK shipping.",
